COVID 19 Analysis¶

Refrences and Acknowledgements

Data:

  • Cumulative count of confirmed, death and recovered cases of COVID-19 from different countries from 22nd January 2020 to 23rd March 2020 https://www.kaggle.com/imdevskp/corona-virus-report#covid_19_clean_complete.csv
  • Cumulative count of confirmed, death and recovered cases of COVID-19 from different States of India from January 30th 2020 to 24th March 2020 https://www.kaggle.com/imdevskp/covid19-corona-virus-india-dataset#complete.csv

Analysis updated on March 24th 2020¶

Analysis will be updated very shortly!!!!

init_notebook_mode(connected=True)

In [10]:
labels = ['Confirmed','Deaths','Recovered']
values = [grouped_data1["Confirmed"].sum(), grouped_data1["Deaths"].sum(),grouped_data1["Recovered"].sum()]

fig = go.Figure(data=[go.Pie(labels=labels, values=values, textinfo='label+percent',
                             insidetextorientation='radial'
                            )])
fig.update_layout(title='Confirmed, Death and Recovered Cases % from {} to {}'.format(data["Date"].min().strftime('%m/%d/%Y'),data["Date"].max().strftime('%m/%d/%Y')))
fig.show()

In [14]:
fig = go.Figure()
fig.add_trace(go.Scatter(x=grouped_data1['Date'], y=grouped_data1['Confirmed'].values,fill='tozeroy',
                    mode='lines+markers',
                    name='Confirmed Cases'))
fig.add_trace(go.Scatter(x=grouped_data1['Date'], y=grouped_data1['Deaths'].values,fill='tozeroy',
                    mode='lines+markers',
                    name='Death Cases'))
fig.add_trace(go.Scatter(x=grouped_data1['Date'], y=grouped_data1['Recovered'].values,fill='tozeroy',
                    mode='lines+markers',
                    name='Recovered Cases'))
fig.update_layout(title='Confirmed, Death and Recovered Cases over time across world.',
                   xaxis_title='Date',
                   yaxis_title='Count')
fig.show()
